ype constants\n75:   - [ ] `TestSeccompProfileTypes` - verify all profile types are non-empty\n76:   - [ ] `TestSeccompProfileTypesUnique` - verify profile types are unique\n77: \n78: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 -run TestDefaultCodeExecutionTimeout` and all constant tests\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ### Task 4: Add validation helper functions (optional but recommended)\n83: - [ ] Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go`\n84: - [ ] Add `ValidateRuntimeType(runtime string) error` function\n85:   - [ ] Check if runtime type matches one of the defined constants\n86:   - [ ] Return descriptive error for invalid runtime type\n87: - [ ] Add `ValidateProtocol(protocol string) error` function\n88:   - [ ] Check if protocol matches one of the defined constants\n89:   - [ ] Return descriptive error for invalid protocol\n90: - [ ] Add `ValidateSeccompProfileType(profileType string) error` function\n91:   - [ ] Check if profile type matches one of the defined constants\n92:   - [ ] Return descriptive error for invalid profile type\n93: - [ ] Add unit tests for validation functions\n94: \n95: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 -run TestValidate` to verify validation functions work correctly\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ### Task 5: Update README.md documentation\n100: - [ ] Update `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md`\n101: - [ ] Document the constants package\n102:   - [ ] Add section on default timeouts\n103:   - [ ] Add section on runtime types\n104:   - [ ] Add section on protocol types\n105:   - [ ] Add section on default resource limits\n106:   - [ ] Add section on seccomp profile types\n107: - [ ] Add example usage of constants in client code\n108: - [ ] Add example of using constants in controller code\n109: - [ ] Document validation helper functions (if implemented)\n110: \n111: **Verification**: Review README.md for completeness and accuracy\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ### Task 6: Update deepcopy.go (if needed)\n116: - [ ] Review `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/deepcopy.go`\n117: - [ ] Verify DeepCopy methods are complete for all shared types\n118: - [ ] Verify no shared type is missing DeepCopy implementation\n119: - [ ] Run existing deepcopy tests to ensure they pass\n120: \n121: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 -run TestDeepCopy` to verify all deepcopy methods work\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Task 7: Add integration test examples\n126: - [ ] Update existing test file `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go`\n127: - [ ] Add test demonstrating constant usage in CodeInterpreter\n128:   - [ ] Create CodeInterpreter using runtime constant\n129:   - [ ] Create CodeInterpreter using timeout constant\n130:   - [ ] Create CodeInterpreter using resource limit constants\n131: - [ ] Add test demonstrating constant usage in AgentRuntime\n132:   - [ ] Create AgentRuntime using session timeout constants\n133: - [ ] Add test demonstrating shared type reuse\n134:   - [ ] Verify SandboxContainerResources works in both CRDs\n135:   - [ ] Verify SandboxEnvVar works in both CRDs\n136: \n137: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to verify all tests pass\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ### Task 8: Verify CRD generation\n142: - [ ] Run `make gen-crd` or equivalent CRD generation command\n143: - [ ] Verify generated CRD YAML files include proper validation\n144:   - [ ] Check CodeInterpreter runtime enum matches constants\n145:   - [ ] Check container port protocol enum matches constants\n146:   - [ ] Check default values match constants\n147: - [ ] Verify CRD YAML files are syntactically correct\n148: - [ ] Commit generated CRD files\n149: \n150: **Verification**: Check generated CRD files in `config/crd/bases/`\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ### Task 9: Run full test suite\n155: - [ ] Run `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` to run all tests\n156: - [ ] Verify all existing tests still pass\n157: - [ ] Verify all new tests pass\n158: - [ ] Run `go build ./pkg/apis/...` to verify package builds\n159: - [ ] Run `go vet ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` for static analysis\n160: \n161: **Verification**: All tests pass with no errors or warnings\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Task 10: Update package documentation\n166: - [ ] Review `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go`\n167: - [ ] Ensure package documentation mentions constants\n168: - [ ] Ensure package documentation mentions shared types\n169: - [ ] Update any inline code comments in types.go to reference constants where appropriate\n170: \n171: **Verification**: Review doc.go and types.go comments for completeness\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ## Summary\n176: \n177: **Total Tasks**: 10\n178: **Estimated Effort**: S (Small) - 2-4 hours\n179: \n180: ### Key Deliverables\n181: 1. `constants.go` - Shared constants for runtime types, protocols, resources, etc.\n182: 2. `constants_test.go` - Unit tests for all constants\n183: 3. Updated `types.go` - Documentation and references to constants\n184: 4. Updated `README.md` - Documentation for constants usage\n185: 5. Validation helpers (optional) - Runtime validation functions\n186: 6. Integration tests - Examples of constant usage in CRD resources\n187: \n188: ### Success Criteria\n189: - All constants are defined and exported\n190: - All constants have corresponding unit tests\n191: - Shared types work correctly in both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n192: - CRD generation succeeds with proper validation\n193: - All existing tests continue to pass\n194: - Code compiles without errors or warnings\n195: \n196: ### Dependencies\n197: - Go 1.24+\n198: - controller-gen v0.17.2 (for CRD generation)\n199: - k8s.io/code-generator v0.34.1 (for client-go generation)\n200: \n201: ### Blocked By\n202: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n203: \n204: ### Blocks\n205: - AR-004 (AgentRuntime Controller) - will use these shared types and constants\n206: - AR-006 (CodeInterpreter Controller) - will use these shared types and constants\n\n(End of file - total 206 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/apis`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: S\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create constants.go file\n- [ ] Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants.go`\n- [ ] Define default timeout constants\n  - [ ] `DefaultCodeExecutionTimeout` = 5 minutes\n  - [ ] `SessionTimeoutDefault` = 15 minutes\n  - [ ] `MaxSessionDurationDefault` = 8 hours\n- [ ] Define runtime type constants\n  - [ ] `RuntimeTypePython` = \"python\"\n  - [ ] `RuntimeTypeJavaScript` = \"javascript\"\n  - [ ] `RuntimeTypeTypeScript` = \"typescript\"\n  - [ ] `RuntimeTypeGo` = \"go\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775841258350,"end":1775841258383}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841258399,"sessionID":"ses_2879d0583ffeuS0IOdyWSENoec","part":{"id":"prt_d7863248c001KnrBGAvhpMUyqG","messageID":"msg_d786319da001NM1a16pNYfgvrB","sessionID":"ses_2879d0583ffeuS0IOdyWSENoec","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6040068c7ac54c6caa0c8fc727199de3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CRD 共享类型与常量 Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: [To be filled during spec definition]\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: [To be filled during spec definition]\n\n(End of file - total 7 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CRD 共享类型与常量 Specification\n\n## Purpose\n[To be filled during spec definition]\n\n## Requirements\n[To be filled during spec definition]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/spec.md","time":{"start":1775841258341,"end":1775841258397}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841258402,"sessionID":"ses_2879d0583ffeuS0IOdyWSENoec","part":{"id":"prt_d786326c2001G5iMJAZnyw6pTm","messageID":"msg_d786319da001NM1a16pNYfgvrB","sessionID":"ses_2879d0583ffeuS0IOdyWSENoec","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-df919b4590f949cc99d4ae5558d8f21a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Design\n2: \n3: **Module**: `pkg/apis`\n4: **Language**: Go\n5: **Size**: S\n6: **Purpose**: Define shared types and constants for CRD resources in the AgentCube project.\n7: \n8: ## Architecture\n9: \n10: ### Package Structure\n11: \n12: ```\n13: pkg/apis/\n14: └── runtime/\n15:     └── v1alpha1/\n16:         ├── constants.go               # Shared constants\n17:         ├── types.go                   # Core type definitions (AgentRuntime + CodeInterpreter + Sandbox types)\n18:         ├── register.go                # Scheme registration\n19:         ├── doc.go                     # Package documentation\n20:         ├── deepcopy.go                # DeepCopy methods (generated)\n21:         └── types_test.go              # Unit tests\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ### Design Principles\n25: \n26: 1. **Single Source of Truth**: Shared types and constants defined once in `v1alpha1` package\n27: 2. **Type Safety**: Strong typing for all runtime configurations\n28: 3. **Extensibility**: Easy to add new runtime types and constants\n29: 4. **Validation**: Kubernetes CRD validation enforces enum constraints\n30: 5. **Backward Compatibility**: Constants support graceful migration to new values\n31: \n32: ### Component Interactions\n33: \n34: ```\n35: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n36: │                   pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1                │\n37: │                                                              │\n38: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n39: │  │  constants.go - Shared Constants                     │  │\n40: │  │  • DefaultTimeouts (DefaultCodeExecutionTimeout)     │  │\n41: │  │  • RuntimeTypes (RuntimeTypePython, etc.)            │  │\n42: │  │  • ResourceLimits (DefaultCPULimit, DefaultMemoryLimit)│ │\n43: │  │  • ProtocolTypes (ProtocolTCP, etc.)                 │  │\n44: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n45: │                          ↓                                  │\n46: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n47: │  │  types.go - Shared Types                             │  │\n48: │  │  • SandboxContainerResources                         │  │\n49: │  │  • SandboxEnvVar                                     │  │\n50: │  │  • SandboxEnvVarSource                               │  │\n51: │  │  • SandboxFieldRef                                   │  │\n52: │  │  • SandboxConfigMapKeyRef                            │  │\n53: │  │  • SandboxSecretKeyRef                               │  │\n54: │  │  • SandboxResourceList                               │  │\n55: │  │  • SandboxContainerPort                              │  │\n56: │  │  • SandboxVolumeMount                                │  │\n57: │  │  • SandboxVolume                                     │  │\n58: │  │  • SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource                       │  │\n59: │  │  • SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource                      │  │\n60: │  │  • SandboxSecretVolumeSource                         │  │\n61: │  │  • SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource          │  │\n62: │  │  • SandboxKeyToPath                                  │  │\n63: │  │  • SandboxResources                                  │  │\n64: │  │  • SandboxProbe                                      │  │\n65: │  │  • SandboxProbeHandler                               │  │\n66: │  │  • SandboxExecAction                                 │  │\n67: │  │  • SandboxTCPSocketAction                            │  │\n68: │  │  • SandboxHTTPGetAction                              │  │\n69: │  │  • SandboxHTTPHeader                                 │  │\n70: │  │  • SandboxSecurityContext                            │  │\n71: │  │  • SandboxCapabilities                               │  │\n72: │  │  • SandboxSeccompProfile                             │  │\n73: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n74: │                          ↓                                  │\n75: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n76: │  │  AgentRuntime Types                                  │  │\n77: │  │  • AgentRuntime                                     │  │\n78: │  │  • AgentRuntimeSpec                                  │  │\n79: │  │  • AgentRuntimeStatus                                │  │\n80: │  │  • AgentRuntimeList                                  │  │\n81: │  │  • SandboxTemplate                                   │  │\n82: │  │  • SandboxMetadata                                   │  │\n83: │  │  • SandboxPodSpec                                    │  │\n84: │  │  • SandboxContainer                                  │  │\n85: │  │  • SandboxAffinity                                   │  │\n86: │  │  • SandboxNodeAffinity                               │  │\n87: │  │  • SandboxPodAffinity                                │  │\n88: │  │  • SandboxPodAntiAffinity                            │  │\n89: │  │  • SandboxToleration                                 │  │\n90: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n91: │                          ↓                                  │\n92: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n93: │  │  CodeInterpreter Types                               │  │\n94: │  │  • CodeInterpreter                                   │  │\n95: │  │  • CodeInterpreterSpec                                │  │\n96: │  │  • CodeInterpreterStatus                              │  │\n97: │  │  • CodeInterpreterList                                │  │\n98: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n99: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n100:                           │\n101:                           │ Imported by\n102:                           ↓\n103: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n104: │              Controllers & Consumers                       │\n105: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐              │\n106: │  │  AgentRuntime    │  │ CodeInterpreter  │              │\n107: │  │  Controller      │  │ Controller       │              │\n108: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘              │\n109: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ## Data Structures\n113: \n114: ### Constants\n115: \n116: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants.go`\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: package v1alpha1\n120: \n121: import \"time\"\n122: \n123: const (\n124: \tDefaultCodeExecutionTimeout = 5 * time.Minute\n125: \n126: \tRuntimeTypePython      = \"python\"\n127: \tRuntimeTypeJavaScript  = \"javascript\"\n128: \tRuntimeTypeTypeScript  = \"typescript\"\n129: \tRuntimeTypeGo          = \"go\"\n130: \n131: \tProtocolTCP  = \"TCP\"\n132: \tProtocolUDP  = \"UDP\"\n133: \tProtocolSCTP = \"SCTP\"\n134: \n135: \tDefaultCPULimit    = \"1\"\n136: \tDefaultMemoryLimit = \"1Gi\"\n137: \n138: \tDefaultCPURequest    = \"100m\"\n139: \tDefaultMemoryRequest = \"128Mi\"\n140: \n141: \tSeccompProfileTypeRuntimeDefault = \"RuntimeDefault\"\n142: \tSeccompProfileTypeUnconfined     = \"Unconfined\"\n143: \tSeccompProfileTypeLocalhost      = \"Localhost\"\n144: \n145: \tSessionTimeoutDefault       = 15 * time.Minute\n146: \tMaxSessionDurationDefault   = 8 * time.Hour\n147: )\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ### Shared Types\n151: \n152: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n153: \n154: The following types are shared between AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter:\n155: \n156: #### Resource Types\n157: \n158: ```go\n159: type SandboxContainerResources struct {\n160: \tLimits   SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n161: \tRequests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n162: }\n163: \n164: type SandboxResourceList struct {\n165: \tCPU              string `json:\"cpu,omitempty\"`\n166: \tMemory           string `json:\"memory,omitempty\"`\n167: \tEphemeralStorage string `json:\"ephemeralStorage,omitempty\"`\n168: }\n169: \n170: type SandboxResources struct {\n171: \tLimits   SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n172: \tRequests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n173: }\n174: ```\n175: \n176: #### Environment Variable Types\n177: \n178: ```go\n179: type SandboxEnvVar struct {\n180: \tName      string                `json:\"name\"`\n181: \tValue     string                `json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n182: \tValueFrom *SandboxEnvVarSource  `json:\"valueFrom,omitempty\"`\n183: }\n184: \n185: type SandboxEnvVarSource struct {\n186: \tFieldRef        *SandboxFieldRef        `json:\"fieldRef,omitempty\"`\n187: \tConfigMapKeyRef *SandboxConfigMapKeyRef `json:\"configMapKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n188: \tSecretKeyRef    *SandboxSecretKeyRef    `json:\"secretKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n189: }\n190: \n191: type SandboxFieldRef struct {\n192: \tFieldPath string `json:\"fieldPath\"`\n193: }\n194: \n195: type SandboxConfigMapKeyRef struct {\n196: \tName     string `json:\"name\"`\n197: \tKey      string `json:\"key\"`\n198: \tOptional *bool   `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n199: }\n200: \n201: type SandboxSecretKeyRef struct {\n202: \tName     string `json:\"name\"`\n203: \tKey      string `json:\"key\"`\n204: \tOptional *bool   `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n205: }\n206: ```\n207: \n208: #### Container Types\n209: \n210: ```go\n211: type SandboxContainerPort struct {\n212: \tName          string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n213: \tContainerPort int32  `json:\"containerPort\"`\n214: \tProtocol      string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n215: \tHostPort      int32  `json:\"hostPort,omitempty\"`\n216: }\n217: ```\n218: \n219: #### Volume Types\n220: \n221: ```go\n222: type SandboxVolumeMount struct {\n223: \tName      string `json:\"name\"`\n224: \tMountPath string `json:\"mountPath\"`\n225: \tSubPath   string `json:\"subPath,omitempty\"`\n226: \tReadOnly  bool   `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\"`\n227: }\n228: \n229: type SandboxVolume struct {\n230: \tName                   string                                   `json:\"name\"`\n231: \tEmptyDir               *SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource             `json:\"emptyDir,omitempty\"`\n232: \tConfigMap              *SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource            `json:\"configMap,omitempty\"`\n233: \tSecret                 *SandboxSecretVolumeSource               `json:\"secret,omitempty\"`\n234: \tPersistentVolumeClaim  *SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource `json:\"persistentVolumeClaim,omitempty\"`\n235: }\n236: \n237: type SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource struct {\n238: \tSizeLimit string `json:\"sizeLimit,omitempty\"`\n239: }\n240: \n241: type SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource struct {\n242: \tName     string             `json:\"name\"`\n243: \tOptional *bool              `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n244: \tItems    []SandboxKeyToPath `json:\"items,omitempty\"`\n245: }\n246: \n247: type SandboxSecretVolumeSource struct {\n248: \tSecretName string             `json:\"secretName\"`\n249: \tOptional   *bool              `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n250: \tItems      []SandboxKeyToPath `json:\"items,omitempty\"`\n251: }\n252: \n253: type SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource struct {\n254: \tClaimName string `json:\"claimName\"`\n255: \tReadOnly  bool   `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\"`\n256: }\n257: \n258: type SandboxKeyToPath struct {\n259: \tKey  string  `json:\"key\"`\n260: \tPath string  `json:\"path\"`\n261: \tMode *int32  `json:\"mode,omitempty\"`\n262: }\n263: ```\n264: \n265: #### Probe Types\n266: \n267: ```go\n268: type SandboxProbe struct {\n269: \tSandboxProbeHandler `json:\",inline\"`\n270: \tInitialDelaySeconds int32 `json:\"initialDelaySeconds,omitempty\"`\n271: \tTimeoutSeconds      int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n272: \tPeriodSeconds       int32 `json:\"periodSeconds,omitempty\"`\n273: \tSuccessThreshold    int32 `json:\"successThreshold,omitempty\"`\n274: \tFailureThreshold    int32 `json:\"failureThreshold,omitempty\"`\n275: }\n276: \n277: type SandboxProbeHandler struct {\n278: \tExec     *SandboxExecAction    `json:\"exec,omitempty\"`\n279: \tTCPSocket *SandboxTCPSocketAction `json:\"tcpSocket,omitempty\"`\n280: \tHTTPGet   *SandboxHTTPGetAction   `json:\"httpGet,omitempty\"`\n281: }\n282: \n283: type SandboxExecAction struct {\n284: \tCommand []string `json:\"command\"`\n285: }\n286: \n287: type SandboxTCPSocketAction struct {\n288: \tPort k8sutil.IntOrString `json:\"port\"`\n289: \tHost string              `json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n290: }\n291: \n292: type SandboxHTTPGetAction struct {\n293: \tPort        k8sutil.IntOrString `json:\"port\"`\n294: \tHost        string              `json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n295: \tPath        string              `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n296: \tScheme      string              `json:\"scheme,omitempty\"`\n297: \tHTTPHeaders []SandboxHTTPHeader `json:\"httpHeaders,omitempty\"`\n298: }\n299: \n300: type SandboxHTTPHeader struct {\n301: \tName  string `json:\"name\"`\n302: \tValue string `json:\"value\"`\n303: }\n304: ```\n305: \n306: #### Security Types\n307: \n308: ```go\n309: type SandboxSecurityContext struct {\n310: \tRunAsUser                *int64                 `json:\"runAsUser,omitempty\"`\n311: \tRunAsGroup               *int64                 `json:\"runAsGroup,omitempty\"`\n312: \tRunAsNonRoot             *bool                  `json:\"runAsNonRoot,omitempty\"`\n313: \tReadOnlyRootFilesystem   *bool                  `json:\"readOnlyRootFilesystem,omitempty\"`\n314: \tAllowPrivilegeEscalation *bool                  `json:\"allowPrivilegeEscalation,omitempty\"`\n315: \tCapabilities             *SandboxCapabilities    `json:\"capabilities,omitempty\"`\n316: \tSeccompProfile           *SandboxSeccompProfile  `json:\"seccompProfile,omitempty\"`\n317: \tPrivileged               *bool                  `json:\"privileged,omitempty\"`\n318: \tProcMount                string                 `json:\"procMount,omitempty\"`\n319: }\n320: \n321: type SandboxCapabilities struct {\n322: \tAdd  []string `json:\"add,omitempty\"`\n323: \tDrop []string `json:\"drop,omitempty\"`\n324: }\n325: \n326: type SandboxSeccompProfile struct {\n327: \tType             string `json:\"type\"`\n328: \tLocalhostProfile string `json:\"localhostProfile,omitempty\"`\n329: }\n330: ```\n331: \n332: ## API Contracts\n333: \n334: ### CRD Validation\n335: \n336: #### CodeInterpreter Runtime Enum\n337: \n338: ```go\n339: // +kubebuilder:default=\"python\"\n340: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=python;javascript;typescript;go\n341: // +optional\n342: Runtime string `json:\"runtime,omitempty\"`\n343: ```\n344: \n345: Supported values:\n346: - `python`\n347: - `javascript`\n348: - `typescript`\n349: - `go`\n350: \n351: #### Timeout Format\n352: \n353: ```go\n354: // +kubebuilder:default=\"5m\"\n355: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n356: // +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n357: // +optional\n358: Timeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"timeout,omitempty\"`\n359: ```\n360: \n361: Valid duration formats:\n362: - `5m` (5 minutes)\n363: - `1h` (1 hour)\n364: - `30s` (30 seconds)\n365: - `1h30m` (1 hour 30 minutes)\n366: \n367: #### Port Validation\n368: \n369: ```go\n370: // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n371: // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n372: ContainerPort int32 `json:\"containerPort\"`\n373: ```\n374: \n375: Port range: 1-65535\n376: \n377: #### Protocol Enum\n378: \n379: ```go\n380: // +kubebuilder:default=TCP\n381: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=TCP;UDP;SCTP\n382: // +optional\n383: Protocol string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n384: ```\n385: \n386: Supported values:\n387: - `TCP`\n388: - `UDP`\n389: - `SCTP`\n390: \n391: ### Constants Usage\n392: \n393: #### Default Values in Controllers\n394: \n395: ```go\n396: import (\n397: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n398: )\n399: \n400: func applyDefaults(ci *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) {\n401: \tif ci.Spec.Runtime == \"\" {\n402: \t\tci.Spec.Runtime = v1alpha1.RuntimeTypePython\n403: \t}\n404: \tif ci.Spec.Timeout == nil {\n405: \t\tci.Spec.Timeout = &metav1.Duration{\n406: \t\t\tDuration: v1alpha1.DefaultCodeExecutionTimeout,\n407: \t\t}\n408: \t}\n409: }\n410: ```\n411: \n412: #### Resource Defaults\n413: \n414: ```go\n415: func applyResourceDefaults(resources *v1alpha1.SandboxContainerResources) {\n416: \tif resources == nil {\n417: \t\tresources = &v1alpha1.SandboxContainerResources{}\n418: \t}\n419: \tif resources.Requests.CPU == \"\" {\n420: \t\tresources.Requests.CPU = v1alpha1.DefaultCPURequest\n421: \t}\n422: \tif resources.Requests.Memory == \"\" {\n423: \t\tresources.Requests.Memory = v1alpha1.DefaultMemoryRequest\n424: \t}\n425: }\n426: ```\n427: \n428: ## Error Handling\n429: \n430: ### Validation Errors\n431: \n432: #### Invalid Runtime Type\n433: \n434: ```go\n435: func validateRuntimeType(runtime string) error {\n436: \tvalidRuntimes := map[string]bool{\n437: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypePython:     true,\n438: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeJavaScript: true,\n439: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeTypeScript: true,\n440: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeGo:         true,\n441: \t}\n442: \n443: \tif !validRuntimes[runtime] {\n444: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"invalid runtime type: %s, must be one of: python, javascript, typescript, go\", runtime)\n445: \t}\n446: \treturn nil\n447: }\n448: ```\n449: \n450: #### Invalid Timeout Format\n451: \n452: ```go\n453: func validateTimeout(timeout *metav1.Duration) error {\n454: \tif timeout == nil {\n455: \t\treturn nil\n456: \t}\n457: \n458: \tif timeout.Duration <= 0 {\n459: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"timeout must be positive, got: %v\", timeout.Duration)\n460: \t}\n461: \n462: \tif timeout.Duration > 24*time.Hour {\n463: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"timeout cannot exceed 24 hours, got: %v\", timeout.Duration)\n464: \t}\n465: \n466: \treturn nil\n467: }\n468: ```\n469: \n470: #### Invalid Port Range\n471: \n472: ```go\n473: func validatePort(port int32) error {\n474: \tif port < 1 || port > 65535 {\n475: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"port must be between 1 and 65535, got: %d\", port)\n476: \t}\n477: \treturn nil\n478: }\n479: ```\n480: \n481: ### Client-Go Error Handling\n482: \n483: ```go\n484: import (\n485: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n486: )\n487: \n488: ci := &v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n489: \tSpec: v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n490: \t\tImage:   \"python:3.11-slim\",\n491: \t\tRuntime: v1alpha1.RuntimeTypePython,\n492: \t},\n493: }\n494: \n495: createdCi, err := client.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create(ctx, ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n496: if err != nil {\n497: \tswitch {\n498: \tcase errors.IsAlreadyExists(err):\n499: \t\tlog.Warn(\"CodeInterpreter already exists\")\n500: \tcase errors.IsInvalid(err):\n501: \t\tlog.Errorf(\"Invalid CodeInterpreter spec: %v\", err)\n502: \tcase errors.IsForbidden(err):\n503: \t\tlog.Errorf(\"Permission denied: %v\", err)\n504: \tdefault:\n505: \t\tlog.Errorf(\"Failed to create CodeInterpreter: %v\", err)\n506: \t}\n507: \treturn err\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ## Testing Strategy\n512: \n513: ### Unit Tests\n514: \n515: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants_test.go` (to be created)\n516: \n517: ```go\n518: package v1alpha1_test\n519: \n520: import (\n521: \t\"testing\"\n522: \t\"time\"\n523: \n524: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n525: )\n526: \n527: func TestDefaultTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n528: \tif v1alpha1.DefaultCodeExecutionTimeout != 5*time.Minute {\n529: \t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected default timeout 5m, got %v\", v1alpha1.DefaultCodeExecutionTimeout)\n530: \t}\n531: }\n532: \n533: func TestRuntimeTypes(t *testing.T) {\n534: \truntimes := []string{\n535: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypePython,\n536: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeJavaScript,\n537: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeTypeScript,\n538: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeGo,\n539: \t}\n540: \n541: \tfor _, runtime := range runtimes {\n542: \t\tif runtime == \"\" {\n543: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Runtime type should not be empty\")\n544: \t\t}\n545: \t}\n546: }\n547: \n548: func TestProtocolTypes(t *testing.T) {\n549: \tprotocols := []string{\n550: \t\tv1alpha1.ProtocolTCP,\n551: \t\tv1alpha1.ProtocolUDP,\n552: \t\tv1alpha1.ProtocolSCTP,\n553: \t}\n554: \n555: \tfor _, protocol := range protocols {\n556: \t\tif protocol == \"\" {\n557: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Protocol type should not be empty\")\n558: \t\t}\n559: \t}\n560: }\n561: \n562: func TestResourceLimits(t *testing.T) {\n563: \tif v1alpha1.DefaultCPULimit == \"\" {\n564: \t\tt.Error(\"DefaultCPULimit should not be empty\")\n565: \t}\n566: \n567: \tif v1alpha1.DefaultMemoryLimit == \"\" {\n568: \t\tt.Error(\"DefaultMemoryLimit should not be empty\")\n569: \t}\n570: }\n571: \n572: func TestSeccompProfileTypes(t *testing.T) {\n573: \tprofiles := []string{\n574: \t\tv1alpha1.SeccompProfileTypeRuntimeDefault,\n575: \t\tv1alpha1.SeccompProfileTypeUnconfined,\n576: \t\tv1alpha1.SeccompProfileTypeLocalhost,\n577: \t}\n578: \n579: \tfor _, profile := range profiles {\n580: \t\tif profile == \"\" {\n581: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Seccomp profile type should not be empty\")\n582: \t\t}\n583: \t}\n584: }\n585: ```\n586: \n587: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go` (existing)\n588: \n589: Existing tests cover:\n590: - AgentRuntime types\n591: - CodeInterpreter types\n592: - Sandbox types\n593: - DeepCopy functionality\n594: - JSON serialization\n595: - Scheme registration\n596: \n597: ### Integration Tests\n598: \n599: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/client_integration_test.go`\n600: \n601: ```go\n602: package v1alpha1_test\n603: \n604: import (\n605: \t\"context\"\n606: \t\"testing\"\n607: \n608: \t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n609: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n610: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n611: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme\"\n612: \n613: \truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n614: )\n615: \n616: var _ = Describe(\"Shared Types Integration\", func() {\n617: \tIt(\"should use shared SandboxContainerResources in CodeInterpreter\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n618: \t\tci := &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n619: \t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n620: \t\t\t\tName:      \"test-ci\",\n621: \t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n622: \t\t\t},\n623: \t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n624: \t\t\t\tImage: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n625: \t\t\t\tResources: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainerResources{\n626: \t\t\t\t\tLimits: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxResourceList{\n627: \t\t\t\t\t\tCPU:    runtimev1alpha1.DefaultCPULimit,\n628: \t\t\t\t\t\tMemory: runtimev1alpha1.DefaultMemoryLimit,\n629: \t\t\t\t\t},\n630: \t\t\t\t},\n631: \t\t\t},\n632: \t\t}\n633: \n634: \t\tif ci.Spec.Resources.Limits.CPU != runtimev1alpha1.DefaultCPULimit {\n635: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected CPU limit %s, got %s\", runtimev1alpha1.DefaultCPULimit, ci.Spec.Resources.Limits.CPU)\n636: \t\t}\n637: \t})\n638: \n639: \tIt(\"should use shared SandboxEnvVar in both CRDs\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n640: \t\tenv := runtimev1alpha1.SandboxEnvVar{\n641: \t\t\tName:  \"API_KEY\",\n642: \t\t\tValueFrom: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxEnvVarSource{\n643: \t\t\t\tSecretKeyRef: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxSecretKeyRef{\n644: \t\t\t\t\tName: \"api-secret\",\n645: \t\t\t\t\tKey:  \"key\",\n646: \t\t\t\t},\n647: \t\t\t},\n648: \t\t}\n649: \n650: \t\tif env.ValueFrom.SecretKeyRef.Name != \"api-secret\" {\n651: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected secret name api-secret, got %s\", env.ValueFrom.SecretKeyRef.Name)\n652: \t\t}\n653: \t})\n654: })\n655: ```\n656: \n657: ### Validation Tests\n658: \n659: ```go\n660: func TestRuntimeTypeValidation(t *testing.T) {\n661: \tvalidRuntimes := []string{\n662: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypePython,\n663: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeJavaScript,\n664: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeTypeScript,\n665: \t\tv1alpha1.RuntimeTypeGo,\n666: \t}\n667: \n668: \tfor _, runtime := range validRuntimes {\n669: \t\terr := validateRuntimeType(runtime)\n670: \t\tif err != nil {\n671: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Runtime type %s should be valid, got error: %v\", runtime, err)\n672: \t\t}\n673: \t}\n674: \n675: \tinvalidRuntime := \"rust\"\n676: \terr := validateRuntimeType(invalidRuntime)\n677: \tif err == nil {\n678: \t\tt.Errorf(\"Runtime type %s should be invalid\", invalidRuntime)\n679: \t}\n680: }\n681: \n682: func TestTimeoutValidation(t *testing.T) {\n683: \ttests := []struct {\n684: \t\tname        string\n685: \t\ttimeout     *metav1.Duration\n686: \t\texpectError bool\n687: \t}{\n688: \t\t{\n689: \t\t\tname:        \"valid timeout\",\n690: \t\t\ttimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 5 * time.Minute},\n691: \t\t\texpectError: false,\n692: \t\t},\n693: \t\t{\n694: \t\t\tname:        \"nil timeout\",\n695: \t\t\ttimeout:     nil,\n696: \t\t\texpectError: false,\n697: \t\t},\n698: \t\t{\n699: \t\t\tname:        \"zero timeout\",\n700: \t\t\ttimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 0},\n701: \t\t\texpectError: true,\n702: \t\t},\n703: \t\t{\n704: \t\t\tname:        \"negative timeout\",\n705: \t\t\ttimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: -5 * time.Minute},\n706: \t\t\texpectError: true,\n707: \t\t},\n708: \t\t{\n709: \t\t\tname:        \"timeout exceeds max\",\n710: \t\t\ttimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 25 * time.Hour},\n711: \t\t\texpectError: true,\n712: \t\t},\n713: \t}\n714: \n715: \tfor _, tt := range tests {\n716: \t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n717: \t\t\terr := validateTimeout(tt.timeout)\n718: \t\t\tif tt.expectError && err == nil {\n719: \t\t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected error, got nil\")\n720: \t\t\t}\n721: \t\t\tif !tt.expectError && err != nil {\n722: \t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected no error, got: %v\", err)\n723: \t\t\t}\n724: \t\t})\n725: \t}\n726: }\n727: \n728: func TestPortValidation(t *testing.T) {\n729: \ttests := []struct {\n730: \t\tname        string\n731: \t\tport        int32\n732: \t\texpectError bool\n733: \t}{\n734: \t\t{\n735: \t\t\tname:        \"valid port\",\n736: \t\t\tport:        8080,\n737: \t\t\texpectError: false,\n738: \t\t},\n739: \t\t{\n740: \t\t\tname:        \"port too low\",\n741: \t\t\tport:        0,\n742: \t\t\texpectError: true,\n743: \t\t},\n744: \t\t{\n745: \t\t\tname:        \"port too high\",\n746: \t\t\tport:        65536,\n747: \t\t\texpectError: true,\n748: \t\t},\n749: \t\t{\n750: \t\t\tname:        \"port boundary min\",\n751: \t\t\tport:        1,\n752: \t\t\texpectError: false,\n753: \t\t},\n754: \t\t{\n755: \t\t\tname:        \"port boundary max\",\n756: \t\t\tport:        65535,\n757: \t\t\texpectError: false,\n758: \t\t},\n759: \t}\n760: \n761: \tfor _, tt := range tests {\n762: \t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n763: \t\t\terr := validatePort(tt.port)\n764: \t\t\tif tt.expectError && err == nil {\n765: \t\t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected error, got nil\")\n766: \t\t\t}\n767: \t\t\tif !tt.expectError && err != nil {\n768: \t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected no error, got: %v\", err)\n769: \t\t\t}\n770: \t\t})\n771: \t}\n772: }\n773: ```\n774: \n775: ## Integration Points\n776: \n777: ### With AgentRuntime Controller\n778: \n779: ```go\n780: import (\n781: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n782: )\n783: \n784: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) reconcilePod(ar *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error {\n785: \tpod := &corev1.Pod{\n786: \t\tSpec: corev1.PodSpec{\n787: \t\t\tContainers: []corev1.Container{\n788: \t\t\t\t{\n789: \t\t\t\t\tResources: corev1.ResourceRequirements{\n790: \t\t\t\t\t\tLimits: corev1.ResourceList{\n791: \t\t\t\t\t\t\tcorev1.ResourceCPU: resource.MustParse(\n792: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tv1alpha1.DefaultCPULimit,\n793: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t),\n794: \t\t\t\t\t\t},\n795: \t\t\t\t\t},\n796: \t\t\t\t},\n797: \t\t\t},\n798: \t\t},\n799: \t}\n800: \treturn nil\n801: }\n802: ```\n803: \n804: ### With CodeInterpreter Controller\n805: \n806: ```go\n807: func (r *CodeInterpreterReconciler) reconcileInterpreter(ci *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) error {\n808: \tif ci.Spec.Timeout == nil {\n809: \t\tci.Spec.Timeout = &metav1.Duration{\n810: \t\t\tDuration: v1alpha1.DefaultCodeExecutionTimeout,\n811: \t\t}\n812: \t}\n813: \n814: \tif ci.Spec.Runtime == \"\" {\n815: \t\tci.Spec.Runtime = v1alpha1.RuntimeTypePython\n816: \t}\n817: \treturn nil\n818: }\n819: ```\n820: \n821: ### With Session Router\n822: \n823: ```go\n824: func (r *Router) getInterpreterTimeout(ci *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) time.Duration {\n825: \tif ci.Spec.Timeout != nil {\n826: \t\treturn ci.Spec.Timeout.Duration\n827: \t}\n828: \treturn v1alpha1.DefaultCodeExecutionTimeout\n829: }\n830: ```\n831: \n832: ## Dependencies\n833: \n834: ### Go Dependencies\n835: \n836: ```go\n837: import (\n838: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n839: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/intstr\"\n840: \t\"time\"\n841: )\n842: ```\n843: \n844: ### Build Tools\n845: \n846: - `controller-gen`: v0.17.2 (for CRD generation)\n847: - `k8s.io/code-generator`: v0.34.1 (for client-go generation)\n848: \n849: ### Makefile Targets\n850: \n851: | Target | Description |\n852: |--------|-------------|\n853: | `gen-crd` | Generate CRD manifests |\n854: | `gen-client` | Generate client-go library |\n855: | `generate` | Generate all code (CRD + deepcopy) |\n856: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n857: | `gen-check` | Verify generated code is up-to-date |\n858: \n859: ## Documentation\n860: \n861: ### Example Usage with Constants\n862: \n863: ```go\n864: package main\n865: \n866: import (\n867: \t\"time\"\n868: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n869: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n870: )\n871: \n872: func createPythonInterpreter() *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter {\n873: \treturn &v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n874: \t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n875: \t\t\tName:      \"python-interpreter\",\n876: \t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n877: \t\t},\n878: \t\tSpec: v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n879: \t\t\tImage: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n880: \t\t\tRuntime: v1alpha1.RuntimeTypePython,\n881: \t\t\tTimeout: &metav1.Duration{\n882: \t\t\t\tDuration: v1alpha1.DefaultCodeExecutionTimeout,\n883: \t\t\t},\n884: \t\t\tResources: &v1alpha1.SandboxContainerResources{\n885: \t\t\t\tLimits: v1alpha1.SandboxResourceList{\n886: \t\t\t\t\tCPU:    v1alpha1.DefaultCPULimit,\n887: \t\t\t\t\tMemory: v1alpha1.DefaultMemoryLimit,\n888: \t\t\t\t},\n889: \t\t\t\tRequests: v1alpha1.SandboxResourceList{\n890: \t\t\t\t\tCPU:    v1alpha1.DefaultCPURequest,\n891: \t\t\t\t\tMemory: v1alpha1.DefaultMemoryRequest,\n892: \t\t\t\t},\n893: \t\t\t},\n894: \t\t},\n895: \t}\n896: }\n897: ```\n898: \n899: ### Shared Type Reuse\n900: \n901: ```go\n902: func createContainerWithDefaults() v1alpha1.SandboxContainer {\n903: \treturn v1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n904: \t\tName:  \"interpreter\",\n905: \t\tImage: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n906: \t\tResources: &v1alpha1.SandboxContainerResources{\n907: \t\t\tLimits: v1alpha1.SandboxResourceList{\n908: \t\t\t\tCPU:    v1alpha1.DefaultCPULimit,\n909: \t\t\t\tMemory: v1alpha1.DefaultMemoryLimit,\n910: \t\t\t},\n911: \t\t},\n912: \t\tEnv: []v1alpha1.SandboxEnvVar{\n913: \t\t\t{\n914: \t\t\t\tName:  \"PYTHON_VERSION\",\n915: \t\t\t\tValue: \"3.11\",\n916: \t\t\t},\n917: \t\t\t{\n918: \t\t\t\tName: \"API_KEY\",\n919: \t\t\t\tValueFrom: &v1alpha1.SandboxEnvVarSource{\n920: \t\t\t\t\tSecretKeyRef: &v1alpha1.SandboxSecretKeyRef{\n921: \t\t\t\t\t\tName: \"api-secret\",\n922: \t\t\t\t\t\tKey:  \"key\",\n923: \t\t\t\t\t},\n924: \t\t\t\t},\n925: \t\t\t},\n926: \t\t},\n927: \t\tSecurityContext: &v1alpha1.SandboxSecurityContext{\n928: \t\t\tRunAsNonRoot: func() *bool { b := true; return &b }(),\n929: \t\t\tSeccompProfile: &v1alpha1.SandboxSeccompProfile{\n930: \t\t\t\tType: v1alpha1.SeccompProfileTypeRuntimeDefault,\n931: \t\t\t},\n932: \t\t},\n933: \t}\n934: }\n935: ```\n936: \n937: ## Security Considerations\n938: \n939: ### Resource Limits\n940: \n941: Default resource limits should be:\n942: - Applied consistently across all interpreters\n943: - Configurable via CRD spec\n944: - Monitored for resource usage\n945: - Prevented from consuming cluster resources\n946: \n947: ### Timeout Enforcement\n948: \n949: Execution timeouts should be:\n950: - Enforced by the PicoD daemon\n951: - Configurable per CodeInterpreter\n952: - Applied to all code execution requests\n953: - Validated against maximum allowed values\n954: \n955: ### Environment Variable Security\n956: \n957: Environment variables from Secrets should:\n958: - Be encrypted at rest\n959: - Only be accessible to authorized service accounts\n960: - Be validated for sensitive patterns\n961: - Be rotated regularly\n962: \n963: ### Runtime Type Validation\n964: \n965: Runtime types must be:\n966: - Explicitly enumerated\n967: - Validated at admission time\n968: - Restricted to approved languages\n969: - Monitored for security vulnerabilities\n970: \n971: ## Future Enhancements\n972: \n973: ### Potential Extensions\n974: \n975: 1. **Custom Runtime Types**: Support for user-defined runtime configurations\n976: 2. **Dynamic Resource Limits**: Per-request resource scaling\n977: 3. **Namespace-level Defaults**: Namespace-specific default configurations\n978: 4. **Resource Quotas**: Integration with Kubernetes resource quotas\n979: 5. **Policy Enforcement**: Validation policies for runtime configurations\n980: 6. **Metrics Integration**: Prometheus metrics for runtime usage\n981: \n982: ### Version Migration Path\n983: \n984: Future migration from v1alpha1 to v1beta1/v1:\n985: 1. Create new constants file `pkg/apis/runtime/v1beta1/constants.go`\n986: 2. Migrate shared types to new version\n987: 3. Implement conversion functions between v1alpha1 and v1beta1\n988: 4. Update CRD to serve both versions\n989: 5. Set v1beta1 as storage version\n990: 6. Update controllers and clients to use v1beta1\n991: 7. Deprecate v1alpha1 after migration period\n\n(End of file - total 991 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Design\n\n**Module**: `pkg/apis`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: S\n**Purpose**: Define shared types and constants for CRD resources in the AgentCube project.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/apis/\n└── runtime/\n    └── v1alpha1/\n        ├── constants.go               # Shared constants\n        ├── types.go                   # Core type definitions (AgentRuntime + CodeInterpreter + Sandbox types)\n        ├── register.go                # Scheme registration\n        ├── doc.go                     # Package documentation\n        ├── deepcopy.go                # DeepCopy methods (generated)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/design.md","time":{"start":1775841258348,"end":1775841258399}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841258418,"sessionID":"ses_2879d0583ffeuS0IOdyWSENoec","part":{"id":"prt_d78632b4a001y1oGKNNvUwwQ7e","messageID":"msg_d786319da001NM1a16pNYfgvrB","sessionID":"ses_2879d0583ffeuS0IOdyWSENoec","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6f83e5b269fd4ba4bf62b84cf85a420f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package v1alpha1\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n5: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/intstr\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: // +genclient\n9: // +genclient:nonNamespaced\n10: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n11: // +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n12: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ar;agentruntime\n13: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n14: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n15: \n16: // AgentRuntime defines a custom resource for managing agent runtime configurations.\n17: // It represents a sandbox orchestration runtime that manages the lifecycle of agent pods.\n18: type AgentRuntime struct {\n19: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n20: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n21: \n22: \tSpec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n23: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n24: }\n25: \n26: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime.\n27: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n28: \t// PodTemplate defines the template for creating sandbox pods.\n29: \t// +required\n30: \tPodTemplate *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\"`\n31: \n32: \t// SessionTimeout defines the timeout for idle sessions before cleanup.\n33: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n34: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n35: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n36: \t// +optional\n37: \tSessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n38: \n39: \t// MaxSessionDuration defines the maximum allowed duration for a session.\n40: \t// +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n41: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n42: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n43: \t// +optional\n44: \tMaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n45: }\n46: \n47: // SandboxTemplate defines the template for creating sandbox pods.\n48: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n49: \t// Metadata defines labels and annotations for the pod.\n50: \t// +optional\n51: \tMetadata *SandboxMetadata `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n52: \n53: \t// Spec defines the pod specification.\n54: \tSpec SandboxPodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n55: }\n56: \n57: // SandboxMetadata defines metadata for sandbox pods.\n58: type SandboxMetadata struct {\n59: \t// Labels are key-value pairs attached to the pod.\n60: \t// +optional\n61: \tLabels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n62: \n63: \t// Annotations are unstructured key-value pairs stored with the pod.\n64: \t// +optional\n65: \tAnnotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n66: }\n67: \n68: // SandboxPodSpec defines the specification for sandbox pods.\n69: type SandboxPodSpec struct {\n70: \t// Containers represents the list of containers in the pod.\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1\n72: \tContainers []SandboxContainer `json:\"containers\"`\n73: \n74: \t// NodeSelector specifies node selection constraints.\n75: \t// +optional\n76: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n77: \n78: \t// Affinity defines pod scheduling constraints.\n79: \t// +optional\n80: \tAffinity *SandboxAffinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n81: \n82: \t// Tolerations defines pod tolerations.\n83: \t// +optional\n84: \tTolerations []SandboxToleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n85: \n86: \t// ResourceRequirements defines resource requirements for the pod.\n87: \t// +optional\n88: \tResourceRequirements *SandboxResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n89: \n90: \t// Volumes defines pod volumes.\n91: \t// +optional\n92: \tVolumes []SandboxVolume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n93: }\n94: \n95: // SandboxContainer defines a container in a sandbox pod.\n96: type SandboxContainer struct {\n97: \t// Name is the name of the container.\n98: \t// +required\n99: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n100: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n101: \n102: \t// Image is the container image.\n103: \t// +required\n104: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n105: \n106: \t// Command specifies the entrypoint array for the container.\n107: \t// +optional\n108: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n109: \n110: \t// Args specifies the arguments to the entrypoint.\n111: \t// +optional\n112: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n113: \n114: \t// WorkingDir specifies the working directory.\n115: \t// +optional\n116: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n117: \n118: \t// Ports represents the network ports exposed by the container.\n119: \t// +optional\n120: \tPorts []SandboxContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n121: \n122: \t// Env represents environment variables.\n123: \t// +optional\n124: \tEnv []SandboxEnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n125: \n126: \t// Resources defines compute resource requirements.\n127: \t// +optional\n128: \tResources *SandboxContainerResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n129: \n130: \t// VolumeMounts specifies volume mounts.\n131: \t// +optional\n132: \tVolumeMounts []SandboxVolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n133: \n134: \t// LivenessProbe defines the liveness probe.\n135: \t// +optional\n136: \tLivenessProbe *SandboxProbe `json:\"livenessProbe,omitempty\"`\n137: \n138: \t// ReadinessProbe defines the readiness probe.\n139: \t// +optional\n140: \tReadinessProbe *SandboxProbe `json:\"readinessProbe,omitempty\"`\n141: \n142: \t// SecurityContext defines security settings.\n143: \t// +optional\n144: \tSecurityContext *SandboxSecurityContext `json:\"securityContext,omitempty\"`\n145: }\n146: \n147: // SandboxContainerPort defines a network port in a container.\n148: type SandboxContainerPort struct {\n149: \t// Name is the name of the port.\n150: \t// +optional\n151: \tName string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n152: \n153: \t// ContainerPort is the port number on the container.\n154: \t// +required\n155: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n156: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n157: \tContainerPort int32 `json:\"containerPort\"`\n158: \n159: \t// Protocol is the protocol for the port.\n160: \t// +optional\n161: \t// +kubebuilder:default=TCP\n162: \tProtocol string `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n163: \n164: \t// HostPort is the port number on the host.\n165: \t// +optional\n166: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n167: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n168: \tHostPort int32 `json:\"hostPort,omitempty\"`\n169: }\n170: \n171: // SandboxEnvVar defines an environment variable.\n172: type SandboxEnvVar struct {\n173: \t// Name is the name of the environment variable.\n174: \t// +required\n175: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n176: \n177: \t// Value is the literal value of the environment variable.\n178: \t// +optional\n179: \tValue string `json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n180: \n181: \t// ValueFrom specifies a source for the value.\n182: \t// +optional\n183: \tValueFrom *SandboxEnvVarSource `json:\"valueFrom,omitempty\"`\n184: }\n185: \n186: // SandboxEnvVarSource defines a source for environment variable values.\n187: type SandboxEnvVarSource struct {\n188: \t// FieldRef selects a field from the pod.\n189: \t// +optional\n190: \tFieldRef *SandboxFieldRef `json:\"fieldRef,omitempty\"`\n191: \n192: \t// ConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n193: \t// +optional\n194: \tConfigMapKeyRef *SandboxConfigMapKeyRef `json:\"configMapKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// SecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n197: \t// +optional\n198: \tSecretKeyRef *SandboxSecretKeyRef `json:\"secretKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n199: }\n200: \n201: // SandboxFieldRef selects a field from a pod.\n202: type SandboxFieldRef struct {\n203: \t// FieldPath is the path of the field.\n204: \t// +required\n205: \tFieldPath string `json:\"fieldPath\"`\n206: }\n207: \n208: // SandboxConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n209: type SandboxConfigMapKeyRef struct {\n210: \t// Name is the name of the ConfigMap.\n211: \t// +required\n212: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n213: \n214: \t// Key is the key to select.\n215: \t// +required\n216: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n217: \n218: \t// Optional specifies whether the ConfigMap must exist.\n219: \t// +optional\n220: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n221: }\n222: \n223: // SandboxSecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n224: type SandboxSecretKeyRef struct {\n225: \t// Name is the name of the Secret.\n226: \t// +required\n227: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n228: \n229: \t// Key is the key to select.\n230: \t// +required\n231: \tKey string `json:\"key\"`\n232: \n233: \t// Optional specifies whether the Secret must exist.\n234: \t// +optional\n235: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n236: }\n237: \n238: // SandboxContainerResources defines resource requirements for a container.\n239: type SandboxContainerResources struct {\n240: \t// Limits defines the resource limits.\n241: \t// +optional\n242: \tLimits SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n243: \n244: \t// Requests defines the resource requests.\n245: \t// +optional\n246: \tRequests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n247: }\n248: \n249: // SandboxResourceList defines a list of resources.\n250: type SandboxResourceList struct {\n251: \t// CPU defines CPU resources.\n252: \t// +optional\n253: \tCPU string `json:\"cpu,omitempty\"`\n254: \n255: \t// Memory defines memory resources.\n256: \t// +optional\n257: \tMemory string `json:\"memory,omitempty\"`\n258: \n259: \t// EphemeralStorage defines ephemeral storage resources.\n260: \t// +optional\n261: \tEphemeralStorage string `json:\"ephemeralStorage,omitempty\"`\n262: }\n263: \n264: // SandboxResources defines resource requirements for the pod.\n265: type SandboxResources struct {\n266: \t// Limits defines the resource limits.\n267: \t// +optional\n268: \tLimits SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n269: \n270: \t// Requests defines the resource requests.\n271: \t// +optional\n272: \tRequests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n273: }\n274: \n275: // SandboxVolumeMount defines a volume mount.\n276: type SandboxVolumeMount struct {\n277: \t// Name is the name of the volume.\n278: \t// +required\n279: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n280: \n281: \t// MountPath is the path within the container.\n282: \t// +required\n283: \tMountPath string `json:\"mountPath\"`\n284: \n285: \t// SubPath is the sub-path within the volume.\n286: \t// +optional\n287: \tSubPath string `json:\"subPath,omitempty\"`\n288: \n289: \t// ReadOnly specifies whether the volume is read-only.\n290: \t// +optional\n291: \tReadOnly bool `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\"`\n292: }\n293: \n294: // SandboxVolume defines a volume.\n295: type SandboxVolume struct {\n296: \t// Name is the name of the volume.\n297: \t// +required\n298: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n299: \n300: \t// EmptyDir defines an empty directory volume.\n301: \t// +optional\n302: \tEmptyDir *SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource `json:\"emptyDir,omitempty\"`\n303: \n304: \t// ConfigMap defines a ConfigMap volume.\n305: \t// +optional\n306: \tConfigMap *SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource `json:\"configMap,omitempty\"`\n307: \n308: \t// Secret defines a Secret volume.\n309: \t// +optional\n310: \tSecret *SandboxSecretVolumeSource `json:\"secret,omitempty\"`\n311: \n312: \t// PersistentVolumeClaim defines a PVC volume.\n313: \t// +optional\n314: \tPersistentVolumeClaim *SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource `json:\"persistentVolumeClaim,omitempty\"`\n315: }\n316: \n317: // SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource defines an empty directory volume.\n318: type SandboxEmptyDirVolumeSource struct {\n319: \t// SizeLimit is the limit on the size of the volume.\n320: \t// +optional\n321: \tSizeLimit string `json:\"sizeLimit,omitempty\"`\n322: }\n323: \n324: // SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource defines a ConfigMap volume.\n325: type SandboxConfigMapVolumeSource struct {\n326: \t// Name is the name of the ConfigMap.\n327: \t// +required\n328: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n329: \n330: \t// Optional specifies whether the ConfigMap must exist.\n331: \t// +optional\n332: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n333: \n334: \t// Items specifies keys to use and the path to mount them at.\n335: \t// +optional\n336: \tItems []SandboxKeyToPath `json:\"items,omitempty\"`\n337: }\n338: \n339: // SandboxSecretVolumeSource defines a Secret volume.\n340: type SandboxSecretVolumeSource struct {\n341: \t// SecretName is the name of the Secret.\n342: \t// +required\n343: \tSecretName string `json:\"secretName\"`\n344: \n345: \t// Optional specifies whether the Secret must exist.\n346: \t// +optional\n347: \tOptional *bool `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n348: \n349: \t// Items specifies keys to use and the path to mount them at.\n350: \t// +optional\n351: \tItems []SandboxKeyToPath `json:\"items,omitempty\"`\n352: }\n353: \n354: // SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource defines a PVC volume.\n355: type SandboxPersistentVolumeClaimVolumeSource struct {\n356: \t// ClaimName is the name of the PVC.\n357: \t// +required\n358: \tClaimName string `json:\"claimName\"`\n359: \n360: \t// ReadOnly specifies whether the volume is read-only.\n361: \t// +optional\n362: \tReadOnly bool `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\"`\n363: }\n364: \n365: // SandboxKeyToPath maps a key to a path.\n366: type SandboxKeyToPath struct {\n367: \t// Key is the key to r